				\begin{document}$$F-measure=\frac{2\ast sensitivity\ast precision}{sensitivity+precision}$$\end{document}F−measure=2∗sensitivity∗precisionsensitivity+precisionwhere true positive (TP) was a head impact that was classified by the classifier as a head impact, true negative (TN) was a nonimpact that was classified by the classifier as a nonimpact, a false positive (FP) was a nonimpact that was classified by the classifier as a head impact, and a false negative (FN) was a head impact that was classified by the classifier as a nonimpact.
